TASK:
Implement a function that accepts an array of integers representing the ASCII Values of characters.
The function must return a string corresponding to the ASCII Values.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE IN C:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
char* asciiToString(int SIZE, int *arr)
{
    char *res=(char*)malloc(SIZE*sizeof(char));
    int k=0;
    for(int i=0;i<SIZE;i++){
        res[k++]=(char)arr[i];
    }
    return res;
}
-------------------------------------------
